JOHANNESBURG &#8211; The South African Reserve Bank (Sarb) said on Tuesday it has filed an application to the High Court challenging a recommendation by the country&#8217;s main anti-graft watchdog to change the bank regulator&#8217;s mandate.Governor Lesetja Kganyago said in court filings that the proposal by Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane to strip the bank&#8217;s mandate of maintaining currency and price stability would undermine Sarb&#8217;s role in keeping the financial system stable. 